        <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">Gas</ENAMEX> Chromatograph <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Mass Spectrometer</ENAMEX> for characterizing organic molecules. The results were
        unexpected (<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Klein</ENAMEX> <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1978, 1999</TIMEX>). There was a detectable reaction in <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">two</NUMEX> of the incubation
        experiments. In the <ENAMEX TYPE="LANGUAGE">‚ÄúGas Exchange‚</ENAMEX>Äù experiment, a burst of <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">oxygen</ENAMEX> was released when the soil
        was exposed to <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">water</ENAMEX>. The <ENAMEX TYPE="LANGUAGE">‚ÄúLabeled Release‚</ENAMEX>Äù experiment showed that organic <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">material</ENAMEX> was
        consumed, and that <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">carbon dioxide</ENAMEX> was released concomitantly. In the <ENAMEX TYPE="PRODUCT">Labeled Release</ENAMEX>
